   Mol. Spectrosc. 74, 294 (1979)]. The final molecular constants for both
   the B(2)Sigma(+) (v = 0-6) and X(2)Sigma(+) (v = 0-10) states were
   obtained from global merge calculations of the present data of the B -->
   X system and previously obtained in our laboratory data for A --> X and
   B --> A systems in the CO+ molecule. Merged molecular parameters have
   been used in order to the determine the equilibrium constants for both
   considered states. The gamma(e) = 2.194(14) x 10(-2) cm(-1) and
   alpha(gammae) = -1.021(64) x 10(-4) cm(-1) constants for th B(2)Sigma(+)
