Month = {FEB},
Abstract = {The emission spectrum of the comet-tail (A2 Pi(i)-X(2)Sigma(+)) system
   of (CO+)-C-12-O-16 produced in the cathode glow of a hollow-cathode
   discharge tube and photographed in the spectral region 3345-8500
   Angstrom at high resolution was reinvestigated. Detailed rotational
   analysis of 10 bands involving 5 vibrational levels v = 0 to 4 of each
   of the A and X states was carried out. Spin-splitting of the rotational
   levels was observed for the analyzed bands. The observed intensity
   distribution of the branches is found to be in good agreement with
   theoretical calculations. Molecular constants for both the A and X
   states were obtained from a global fit of the present data of the A-X
   system and the infrared and microwave data available from the literature
   for v = 0, 1, 2, 3, and 4 of state X, using effective Hamiltonian for
   the A(2)Pi state and matrix elements for both A and X states. The
   present work suggests that the A(2)Pi(i) state changes from Hund's case
   (a) at low J values to Hund's case (b) at high J values. (C) 2000
   Academic Press.},
